calhost:8888/cbiwv/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/Roots-18.jpg" alt="Wheeling Location" width="315" height="220" /></a></span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #cf202e;">2003</span> | Capitol Business Interiors expands its territory and purchases a new office space in Wheeling, WV.\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #cf202e;"><a href="http://localhost:8888/cbiwv/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/Roots-15.jpg"><img class="alignright size-full wp-image-1276" src="http://localhost:8888/cbiwv/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/Roots-15.jpg" alt="Janet Joseph Clayman honored as a Young Gun" width="315" height="220" /></a></span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #cf202e;">2001</span> | Janet Joseph Clayman is recognized by WV Executive as a Young Gun leading the way in interior design and contract furniture for the state of West Virginia.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #cf202e;"><a href="http://localhost:8888/cbiwv/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/Roots-19.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-1287" src="http://localhost:8888/cbiwv/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/Roots-19.jpg" alt="Chapman Industries Logo" width="315" height="220" /></a></span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #cf202e;">1998</span> | Capitol Business Interiors is acquired by Champion Industries, Inc., making Janet Joseph Clayman the corporation''s first female division manager.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #cf202e;"><a href="http://localhost:8888/cbiwv/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/Roots-20.jpg"><img class="alignright size-full wp-image-1289" src="http://localhost:8888/cbiwv/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/Roots-20.jpg" alt="Janet Joseph Clayman" width="315" height="220" /></a></span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #cf202e;">1997</span> | Janet Joseph Clayman becomes President of Capitol Business Interiors.\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #cf202e;"><a href="http://localhost:8888/cbiwv/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/Roots-3.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-1256" src="http://localhost:8888/cbiwv/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/Roots-3.jpg" alt="Old Captiol Business Interiors Logo" width="315" height="220" /></a></span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #cf202e;">1994</span> | Capitol Business Interiors partners with John Auge, a local graphic designer, to design a new logo that would reflect movement and modernize the existing logo.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #cf202e;"><a href="http://localhost:8888/cbiwv/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/Roots-4.jpg"><img class="alignright size-full wp-image-1257" src="http://localhost:8888/cbiwv/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/Roots-4.jpg" alt="Brenda Tilson and Janet Joseph" width="315" height="220" /></a></span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #cf202e;">1992</span> | Capitol Business Interiors names Brenda Tilson the President and Janet Joseph the Vice President, making it a woman-owned &amp; operated business.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #cf202e;"><a href="http://localhost:8888/cbiwv/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/Roots-2.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-1255" src="http://localhost:8888/cbiwv/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/Roots-2.jpg" alt="New building for Capitol Business Interiors" width="315" height="220" /></a></span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #cf202e;">1990</span> | After a five year search, Jim and Brenda Tilson broke ground for the new 35,000 square foot corporate headquarters on Charleston''s west side where it remains today.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #cf202e;"><a href="http://localhost:8888/cbiwv/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/Roots-5.jpg"><img class="alignright size-full wp-image-1258" src="http://localhost:8888/cbiwv/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/Roots-5.jpg" alt="Old Capitol Business Interiors Logo" width="31